<TITLE> Road crash wipes out 6 of a family in Patia </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, Nov 13 (bdnews24.com)Seven people--six of them of a family--were killed and 10 injured on Friday when a microbus collided head-on with a truck at Patia Upazila. The microbus was carrying them to their home Gairala village in Patia from a wedding ceremony in Lohagarha Upazila. Patia Police Station sub-inspector Mizanur Rahman said the microbus crashed into an oncoming truck in front of the Shahchan Aulia's Mazar (shrine) gate on Chittagong-Cox's Bazaar highway early in the morning. Selim told bdnews24.com, "The microbus met an oncoming truck head-on at around 4am. Four people died on the spot." Tejendra Dhar, 70, Babul Dhar, 50, Bidhu Dhar, 45, and Shahidul, 20, died on the spot. Ten other microbus travellers were taken to the Chittagong Medical College Hospital with serious injuries. Patia police chief Mohiuddin Selim told bdnews24.com injured Mridul Dhar died on the way to the hospital. Later, Sarathi Dhar, 60, and Jadu Dhar, 40, from Gairala village, were also declared dead by the on-duty doctors. The injured including the driver, Shahidul, are under treatment at the hospital. bdnews24
